30/12/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish jets continued bombing terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) bases in northern Iraq on Monday (December 29th), Turkish media reported. 
Warplanes bombed the Hakurke region Monday, following up Sunday's air strikes on several PKK targets in the districts of Khwakurk and Khnera.
In other news, a policeman injured in a blast in Istanbul earlier this month died in hospital on Monday. 
Husnu Uyan, 28, suffered ultimately fatal injuries in the explosion at the entrance of an office of the ruling Justice and Development Party in Istanbul's Sisli district on December 1st. 
The blast injured nine other people. 
(Dogan news agency, Hurriyet, NTV - 29/12/08)
